org.jboss.aerogear.android.pipe.callback

Class AbstractFragmentCallback<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jboss.aerogear.android.pipe.callback.AbstractCallback<T>
      • org.jboss.aerogear.android.pipe.callback.AbstractFragmentCallback<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of data to be passed on onSuccess
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.jboss.aerogear.android.core.Callback<T>

    public abstract class AbstractFragmentCallback<T>
extends AbstractCallback<T>
    LoaderPipe which consume callbacks of this type will supply it with a Activity instance before onSuccess or onFailure are called. This should not be done by the user. These calls are not guaranteed to be thread safe. Instances of the callback should not be shared among Activities and Fragments. After onSuccess or onFailure have been called, the fragment will be set to null.
